  "internal_thinking": "The current game phase is SETUP_FIRST_ROUND, and I have just placed my initial settlement at Node 41. My task is to place a road adjacent to this settlement. My settlement at Node 41 provides access to Hex 17 (Ore 5), Hex 14 (Wheat 9), and Hex 13 (Brick 10). To expand my road network and build additional settlements, I will primarily need Wood and Brick resources. I will analyze the three possible road placements from Node 41:\n\n1.  **Road to Node 40**: Node 40 is connected to Hex 17 (Ore 5) and Hex 13 (Brick 10), and crucially, it offers a Wood 2:1 port. While a port is valuable, my current settlement does not produce Wood. This means I would need to acquire Wood through trades or by expanding to a Wood-producing hex to fully utilize this port. It doesn't immediately address my need for Wood production.\n\n2.  **Road to Node 42**: Node 42 is connected to Hex 18 (Ore 5), Hex 17 (Ore 5), and Hex 14 (Wheat 9). This node offers strong future production of Ore and Wheat. While excellent for building cities and development cards, it does not provide Wood or additional Brick, which are essential for building more roads and settlements in the early game.\n\n3.  **Road to Node 31**: Node 31 is connected to Hex 13 (Brick 10), Hex 9 (Wood 11), and Hex 8 (Brick 10). This node offers significant production of both Wood (from Hex 9, a desirable 11 roll) and Brick (from Hexes 13 and 8, both 10 rolls). This directly complements my existing Brick production and introduces Wood production, which is exactly what I need for rapid expansion of my road network and for building future settlements. This will allow me to access more resources and potentially secure Longest Road.\n\nBased on this analysis, placing the road from Node 41 to Node 31 is the optimal choice. It prioritizes the acquisition of Wood and Brick, which are critical for early game expansion and securing a strong resource engine for future settlements and roads.",
  "note_to_self": "My initial settlement at Node 41 provides Ore, Wheat, and Brick. The road to Node 31 will give me access to Wood (W11) and more Brick (B10), which is crucial for building more roads and settlements. Next turn, I should aim to build a settlement on a sheep-producing hex to complete my resource set for settlement building. Watch out for opponent's placements, especially on high-production Wood/Brick/Sheep hexes.",
  "say_outloud": "Alright, time to lay down some road and start building my empire!",
